## Design decisions (O9.1 — will render into RESULT.md)

- D1. Transport stub = PATH-shadowed curl in harness (kit precedent): the
  production code path (curl → api.telegram.org) stays 100% honest; the fake
  curl parses the URL, enforces the token, serves updates from a file and
  appends sends to sent.jsonl. Zero ports anywhere (H3 lsof).
- D2. Listener = single-pass plain script under launchd StartInterval=30s +
  lock file. 30s cadence + one-pass processing sustains ack ≤1 min with
  margin; no resident process, no daemon pretense (INFO-032 честная
  асинхронность). Test hooks: QROKY_TEST_DELAY_INBOX (sleep between tmp and
  rename), QROKY_TEST_ONESHOT.
- D3. JSON parsing via /usr/bin/python3 one-shot helper inside the script
  (dependency answered in checklist 7). The listener stays a plain script;
  python is a parser, not an agent.
- D4. Inbox conventions: decisions/inbox/ one event per file
  (NNNN-<kind>-<id>.md, YAML frontmatter + body), .tmp.* prefix + mv for
  atomicity; consumed = mv to decisions/inbox/done/ (CEO-orders ledger
  pattern); foreign chat_id → decisions/inbox/quarantine/. Promises = kind:
  promise files in the same inbox.
- D5. Decision parity by construction: ONE renderer (record-decision.sh)
  called by the telegram pickup AND by a session answering in-chat; the
  channel argument is the only varying field → H1 diff = channel line only.
- D6. Digest dedup: send-event.sh appends every sent event id to
  state/signaled/YYYY-MM-DD; digest.sh reads today's registry and renders
  those as status lines, never alarms (H6).
- D7. Quiet hours: send-event.sh checks the profile window; events inside it
  go to state/queue/ (blocker flag preserved); the listener pass flushes the
  queue when quiet hours end — blockers first (H14). User messages are acked
  regardless (human initiated).
- D8. NARRATIVE feed: listener pass sweeps products/*/NARRATIVE.md with a
  per-file byte offset in state/narrative/; profile level 1 = gates only (no
  beats), 2 = beats, 3 = full; rides the dialogue contour через send-event
  (kind=beat, respects quiet hours; open detail per INFO-033 п.6).
- D9. Digest ±5 min proven via the launchd StartCalendarInterval assertion
  (explicitly allowed by H6): install.sh generates the plist from
  profile.conf DIGEST_TIME; harness asserts plist time == profile time and
  the daily (7-day) coverage.
- D10. «расход» section: rendered from state/spend/YYYY-MM-DD ledger when
  present, else the honest line «расход: данных за сегодня нет» — no
  invented numbers (EC6).
- D11. Risk-word: event flagged risk=1 by the CALLER (session/heartbeat owns
  risk classification); send helper then refuses buttons and names the
  required word (default ПОДТВЕРЖДАЮ, profile-overridable); handler rejects
  callback-style answers to risk items and re-asks (H5).
- D12. Sandboxing: all repo-root-relative paths resolve through
  QROKY_TG_ROOT (default: script location → repo root) so the harness runs
  against a throwaway fake repo; production needs no env at all.
- D13. Binding acquisition: install.sh offers a bind step — polls once,
  shows the incoming chat_id, operator confirms, writes state/chat_id.
  Until bound, listener quarantines everything (deny-by-default).

