## Build story

Built runtime/claude/telegram/: lib.sh (profile/token/API/atomic/quiet-hours),
listener.sh (single 30s pass: ack -> durable inbox -> wake; narrative sweep;
queue flush), handler.sh (the only LLM home: kroky, router with ONE re-ask,
promise keeping), pickup.sh (mechanical exactly-once consumption -> parity
records), send-event.sh (THE shared helper: session + heartbeat callers,
quiet queue, risk-word rule, signaled registry), record-decision.sh (ONE
renderer, both channels), digest.sh (4 sections + changelog + dedup),
install.sh/uninstall.sh + 2 launchd plists (listener StartInterval=30;
digest StartCalendarInterval from profile), README.md, profile.conf.example,
dry-run.sh (11 scenarios).

Bug trail (all caught by my own harness, none reached a committed green run
uncorrected):
1. tg_api ok-check string-matched '"ok":true' but the stub emitted
   '"ok": true' (space) — every call "failed", retried x3, queued. Fixed with
   a whitespace-tolerant grep; real Bot API emits the compact form, both now
   accepted. Found because the FIRST full run was 1/11 — the harness earned
   its keep immediately.
2. bash unbound-variable crash on «$label» — a variable immediately followed
   by a multibyte char (») parsed as part of the name under set -u. Fixed
   with ${label}; grep-audited all scripts for the pattern (1 occurrence).
3. Missing executable bits on record-decision.sh/send-event.sh cascaded
   через set -e: pickup died at render, listener beats never sent. chmod +x
   all; found via 9-failure run 2.
4. Quarantine filename collided within one second for two foreign updates
   (second overwrote first) — update_id added to the name. Plus one harness
   self-fix: the done-ledger glob *-kroky-*.md also matched the promise file
   whose work-id contains "kroky" (assertion, not product code).

