## Fix round — after blind verify ACCEPT r1 (VERDICT.md: 0 blocking, 6 minor)

2026-07-10T14:25:00Z fix round opened per coordinator instruction; budget ~50k.
All six findings accepted as valid. Per finding:
- M1 (send-event.sh): callback_data = "<id>|<button-index>" (64-BYTE cap
  checked in bytes at build time; an oversized ID fails LOUDLY, never queues);
  button labels persisted as buttonN: lines in state/pending-gates/<id>;
  listener resolves the verbatim label from the registry at press time —
  verbatim is now exact by construction at any label length. Unknown
  gate/button press → polite reply + log, no record.
- M2 (listener.sh): lock carries the holder PID; a dead holder is stolen
  IMMEDIATELY (kill -0 check), pid-less young locks fall back to a 2-min
  mtime bound. Crash blind window is now one 30s cadence, not ~5.5 min.
- M3 (handler.sh): orphan-promise detector checks THE promise's own work
  file ($INBOX/<work>.md), not "any traffic" — an orphan can no longer hide
  behind unrelated inbox files.
- M4 (listener.sh): digest safety net — sent-marker absent AND now past
  DIGEST_TIME → the pass re-fires digest.sh (idempotent via its own marker).
  Covers both a failed fire and a Mac asleep at fire time; a transient
  outage now costs minutes, not the day.
- M5 (lib.sh): curl stderr captured per attempt, token masked to
  bot****<last4> BEFORE anything reaches telegram.log — the run.log
  checklist answer 4 claim («log line shows bot<masked>») is now TRUE in
  code, closing the record/code discrepancy the verifier found. CORRECTION
  for the record: at build time that claim described intent, not code — the
  verifier was right; behavior was safe (nothing logged) but the claim was
  ahead of the implementation.
- M6 (digest.sh): «Ждёт тебя сегодня» renders one combined list; «решений
  не ждём» appears only when BOTH waiting atoms and pending gates are empty.

Harness: stub upgraded to model the REAL Bot API 64-byte callback_data cap
(oversized → BUTTON_DATA_INVALID, unrecorded) and to force token-bearing
curl stderr failures on demand (fail-remaining hook). Scenario 2 extended:
the crashed pass's lock is deliberately LEFT and the next pass must steal it
(lock-left asserted =1 so the check cannot pass vacuously). New scenarios:
12-long-label (old scheme needs 111 bytes — asserted >64; stub rejection
proven live; press by index; recorded answer = full label verbatim),
13-digest-retry (nothing before DIGEST_TIME, missed fire recovered after;
M6 coherence asserted on the same digest), 14-masked-error (3 forced
failures with token in stderr → >=3 masked bot****<last4> lines, zero raw
tokens in log and across all transcripts; ladder queued, next pass
delivered). Existing callback fixtures moved to the index format.

