## Fix round r2 — RETURN on R2-1 (double-press poison pill), surgical fix

2026-07-10T14:45:00Z r2 verdict read: M2-M6 confirmed fixed, M1 core fixed,
but my M1 guard branch carried a NEW blocking regression. HONEST CORRECTION:
the r1 fix-round claim «a press with no matching registry entry gets a polite
reply and no record» was FALSE AS IMPLEMENTED — the polite branch existed but
was unreachable: on a missing registry file the sed pipeline failed under
set -euo pipefail and killed the pass BEFORE the guard and BEFORE the offset
advance, so an owner-normal double-tap (or a press on an answered gate, whose
registry pickup renames to .answered while buttons stay on the old message)
became a permanent poison pill: the same callback re-crashed every 30s pass.
I wrote the guard and never exercised its failure leg — the exact defect
class the verifier exists to catch, third lesson of this kind (101-r1 F1/F5,
now R2-1).

Fix (listener.sh handle_callback):
1. idx validated as numeric ([[ "$idx" =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]]) BEFORE it touches the
   sed expression (also covers old-format callback data with «/»);
2. the registry lookup runs only when idx is numeric AND the file exists,
   and the pipeline is failure-tolerant (|| true) — the polite decline is
   now genuinely reachable;
3. both decline paths: polite reply sent, NO record, offset advances, pass
   exits 0.

Harness: scenario 15 added — (a) TRUE double-tap flow (fresh gate, legit
press, pickup answers → registry .answered, press the same button again),
(b) press on scenario-1's long-answered gate, (c) two malformed callbacks
(«Да/принять» with a sed-breaking slash; pipe-less junk). Asserts: 4 polite
declines, zero new records, rc 0 on every pass, offset == last update id,
and the contour answers /status right after. Falsifiability: each assertion
maps 1:1 onto the verifier's pre-fix repro (rc=1, offset frozen, 0 replies)
— pre-fix code fails every leg.

Full re-run: 15/15 PASS, first attempt after the fix.

